cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.HC 

The paper deals with image segmentation and classification using machine learning techniques, which are commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of texture and color features for classification suggests the involvement of information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. The study also involves the evaluation of different segmentation methods, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the study aims to improve the efficiency of reviewing medical images, which can be related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
